						               													<description>TRITT RELOADED is a reimplementation of TRITT, that was solved in 2009.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;This new set of rules fixes the problem and also changes the game experience completely, as now lines of 3 or more dots can only be created as a result of a tritton movement. It also includes more pieces than its predecessor.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;COMPONENTS&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A hexagonal board with 91 connected dots.&amp;#10;20 trittons (10 of each type).&amp;#10;Carrying case.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;RULES&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game begins with an empty board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player has an allocated colour (Orange or Blue) and takes all the trittons that have their colour in the middle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The Orange player starts the game by entering one of his trittons somewhere on the board. The three dots of the tritton must be placed over 3 free aligned dots on the board.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;From now on, and starting with the Blue player, players in turn must do these 2 things in order:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Legally enter one of his trittons on the board.&amp;#10;     (Optional) Move an opponent&amp;rsquo;s tritton (if any) any number of steps along the line it is laying on.&amp;#10;     It is forbidden to enter a tritton on the board so that a line of 3 or more dots of the same colour is created. Lines of 3 or more dots can only be created as a result of a tritton movement.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;As a rule of the thumb, you place trittons that have your colour in the middle, and move those that have your colour on the sides.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;END OF GAME&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends in one of the following cases:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;One player wins by making a line of three (or more) dots of his colour but not making a line of at least three dots of the opponent&amp;rsquo;s colour at the same time.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;One player loses by making a line of three dots of the opponent&amp;rsquo;s colour.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;One of the players loses by not being able to make a legal action.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game ends in a tie at any moment if both players agree.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;-description from designer&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
